    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001070_0001" n="0001"/>
<opener>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="1" unit="words"/><date when="1857-07-31"><subst><del>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi></del><add place="over-text">July 31<hi rend="sup">st</hi> </add></subst>
</date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
</opener>

<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I shall be
<lb/>extremely obliged
<lb/>by your giving
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Ford</persName> instructions
<lb/>to draw the <term type="insect">Tsetse</term>	
<lb/>on wood (a small <add place="below">block</add>
<lb/><add place="marginbottom"><persName>J.E. Grey <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName></add>

	<pb facs="liv_001070_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>to be inserted in
<lb/>the page) If it
<lb/>is inconvenient 
<lb/>to do it on wood
<lb/>then a drawing
<lb/>on paper which
<lb/>could be transferred
<lb/>to wood will
<lb/>suit us. I should
<lb/>like it the size

	<pb facs="liv_001070_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>of life and the
<lb/>wings in the 
<lb/>natural position
<lb/>&amp; another <unclear cert="low">equal to</unclear>
<lb/>the wings open
<lb/>to <choice><orig>shew</orig><reg>show</reg></choice> the	
<lb/>yellow bars
<lb/>across the
<lb/>after part of the
<lb/>body - the wings
<lb/>project beyond
<lb/>this part in this	

	<pb facs="liv_001070_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>natural position
<lb/><figure><figDesc>Small sketch of the tsetse's natural position</figDesc></figure></p>
<lb/><p>Please send it
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Cooke</persName> <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Murray</persName>'s cousin	
<lb/>as that gentleman is
<lb/>at present absent
<lb/>He is at this address
<lb/>I thank you most
<lb/>heartily for your
<lb/>prompt attention
<lb/>to my request</p>
<lb/><p>I am to you obliged
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>


            </div>
        </body>
